Installation:
  Deploy:
    /etc/init.d/dirtoshm
    /usr/bin/dirtoshmConfig
    /usr/bin/toRAM
    /usr/bin/toDisk
    /usr/share/applications/dirtoshmConfig.desktop

Removal:
  PreRm:
    Configure ramdirs to "", make sure all .backup dirs are deleted (by calling dirtoshmConfig "")
    Stop Service
  Remove files but:
    /etc/dirtoshmConfig/ramdirs
  PostRm:
    if Purging:
      Remove /etc/dirtoshmConfig
    Update rc.d service & Reload systemctl deamon

Update/Reinstallation:
  PreRm:
    Stop Service
  Deploy:
    /etc/init.d/dirtoshm
    /usr/bin/dirtoshmConfig
    /usr/bin/toRAM
    /usr/bin/toDisk
    /usr/share/applications/dirtoshmConfig.desktop
  PostRm:
    Update rc.d service & Reload systemctl deamon
    Start service


dirtoshmConfig:
  This is the user interface. It should interact with the user and offer --help
  Ensure root
  Stop service
  Read new ramdirs if not argument
  Check for ~ and relative paths
  Use ~ as field sperator to allow for paths containing spaces
  Overwrite old /etc/dirtoshmConfig/ramdirs
  Remove dir.backup if no longer ramdir
  Update rc.d service & Reload systemctl deamon
  Start service


















##Old version with RAMDIRS saved into init.d script


Installation:
  PreInst: NOTHING
  Deploy:
    /etc/dirtoshmConfig/dirtoshm_default
    /usr/bin/dirtoshmConfig
    /usr/bin/toRAM
    /usr/bin/toDisk
    /usr/share/applications/dirtoshmConfig.desktop
  PostInst:
    Move dirtoshm_default to /etc/init.d
    Configure ramdirs

Removing:
  PreRm:
    Stop Service
    Save current RAMDIRS as one line to /etc/dirtoshmConfig/ramdirs
  Remove files but:
    /etc/dirtoshmConfig/ramdirs
    /etc/init.d/dirtoshm
  PostRm:
    Remove /etc/init.d/dirtoshm
    Rename RAMDIRS (remove .backup suffix (TODO: write script which is used when removing ramdirs))
    if Purging:
      Remove /etc/dirtoshmConfig

Updating:
  PreRm:
    Stop Service
    Save current RAMDIRS as one line to /etc/dirtoshmConfig/ramdirs
  PreInst: NOTHING
  Deploy:
    /etc/dirtoshmConfig/dirtoshm_default
    /usr/bin/dirtoshmConfig
    /usr/bin/toRAM
    /usr/bin/toDisk
    /usr/share/applications/dirtoshmConfig.desktop
  PostRm:
    Remove old /etc/init.d/dirtoshm
  PostInst:
    Move dirtoshm_default to /etc/init.d
    Retrieve saved ramdirs and write them into init.d script
